{"type":"message","id":"f8c1a87c","parentId":"918dc0aa","timestamp":"2026-02-18T23:00:00.220Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:10a19bb7-7afb-4b24-8478-62555b540c2d daily-ping-telegram] Send the daily ping to Telegram (ID: 1087368827). Fetch: 1) Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API (https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true), 2) Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance, 3) Top 5 GitHub repos by stars (https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5). Format as a concise morning summary with emoji and send via message tool to Telegram target 1087368827.\nCurrent time: Thursday, February 19th, 2026 — 7:00 AM (Asia/Singapore)"}],"timestamp":1771455600216}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd891e7a","parentId":"f8c1a87c","timestamp":"2026-02-18T23:01:22.458Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to execute a cron job that sends a daily ping to Telegram. I need to:\n\n1. Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API\n2. Fetch stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance\n3. Fetch top 5 GitHub repos by stars\n4. Format everything as a concise morning summary with emoji\n5. Send to Telegram target 1087368827\n\nLet me start by gathering all the","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:0","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\n\nstocks = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\ndata = {}\n\nfor symbol in stocks:\n    try:\n        ticker = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n        hist = ticker.history(period='2d')\n        if len(hist) >= 2:\n            prev_close = hist['Close'].iloc[-2]\n            current = hist['Close'].iloc[-1]\n            change = ((current - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100\n            data[symbol] = {\n                'price': round(current, 2),\n                'change': round(change, 2)\n            }\n        else:\n            info = ticker.info\n            data[symbol] = {\n                'price': round(info.get('currentPrice', 0), 2),\n                'change': round(info.get('regularMarketChangePercent', 0), 2)\n            }\n    except Exception as e:\n        data[symbol] = {'price': 'N/A', 'change': 0, 'error': str(e)}\n\nprint(json.dumps(data, indent=2))\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":9077,"output":482,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9559,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771455600219}}
