{"type":"message","id":"05067ea8","parentId":"84456d1c","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:37:18.633Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:10a19bb7-7afb-4b24-8478-62555b540c2d daily-ping-telegram] Send the daily ping to Telegram (ID: 1087368827). Fetch: 1) Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API (https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true), 2) Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance, 3) Top 5 GitHub repos by stars (https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5). Format as a concise morning summary with emoji and send via message tool to Telegram target 1087368827.\nCurrent time: Thursday, February 19th, 2026 — 9:37 AM (Asia/Singapore)"}],"timestamp":1771465038628}}
{"type":"message","id":"b36c627d","parentId":"05067ea8","timestamp":"2026-02-19T01:38:52.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" I got Bitcoin data and GitHub data, but yfinance failed. Let me try to fetch stock data using an alternative API, perhaps using Alpha Vantage or a free stock API. Actually, let me try installing yfinance first, or use the yahoo finance API directly via web fetch.\n\nActually, let me check if there's a pip install option or use the yfinance library that's available. Let me try an alternative approach - using Alpha Vantage or simply fetching from Yahoo Finance via web scrape/API.\n\nActually, let me try installing yfinance first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Let me install yfinance and try fetching the"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip install yfinance -q","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":19772,"output":152,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19924,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771465038632}}
